org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.utils

Class SortedLinkedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.cloudbus.foggatewaylib.utils.SortedLinkedList<E>
  • Type Parameters:
    E - the type of the elements
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<E>, java.util.Collection<E>
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    SortedDataList

    public class SortedLinkedList<E extends java.lang.Comparable>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.Collection<E>
    Implementation of a sorted linked list, based on the LinkedList. Elements are sorted in ascending order according to their Comparable interface. Despite the name, this class does not have the List interface since some methods would not make sense. Anyways, some more advanced methods are present from Deque, like getFirst(), getLast(), removeFirst(), removeLast(), and other methods from List, like descendingIterator(). null elements are not allowed.
    Author:
    Riccardo Mancini
    See Also:
    LinkedList
